<br>
The reason I can see a problem with allowing a guild to have all week with ntov is because then there is no guarentee the spawns will all be killed in the same time period. If you kill half the dragons, come back 3 days later and kill the last half, then the NEXT guild in rotation will have to wait 3 days from the start of their rotation to kill the same last half of the dragons. Now with the current one (which should probably be extended to 36 hours to ensure that all guild time periods can have a chance to kill everything in tov at once. Not sure how most EST guilds did it, but with a good chance that only half of ntov is spawned by 8pm est, they would need to wait for the next day at 8est, which by that time the 24 hour timer is up and other guilds can move in). the dragon spawnings are somewhat guarenteed to be killed in the same 24 hour period, because if any are left up, they will be immedietly killed by another guild. <br>
<br>
I can really see how extended periods of no patching could really screw up the spawns. If a spawn gets screwed, the guild &quot;up next&quot; should probably have the option of not having their timer start untill all dragons are up. This will give the guild the chance to kill them all, and get all the dragons back on the same schedual.  <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.twcny.rr.com/jeffd/sig713.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cerranshaun>cerranshaun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:blue;'>Tavern Regular</span></span><br>  Posts: 232<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(7/25/03 1:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntaverncommonsroom.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5265.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.moviefanonline.com/iB_html/non-cgi/avatars/uploaded_Morbo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: drop the rotation</span><hr size=1> Now that Idea I like Lum. It sucks having to spend a whole week in NtoV because the dragons spawn 2 on tuesday, 2 on wednesday, 3 friday ect ect. I'd way prefer to pop all the dragons in one day or at least 75% in one day. That way we can be finished with NtoV quickly (which is pretty boring after you've done it a few times) . <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=23503" target="top">Cerranshaun Lightbringer</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
